1
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:13,667
Emma, help yourself first.

2
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:16,300
Let's focus first on how
you can get out of here.

3
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:17,600
Who do you love more?

4
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:19,000
Is it Emma or me?

5
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:21,233
You do this to me
because I'm worthless!

6
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:24,033
We received a complaint
against you.

7
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:28,600
And as per protocol,
we came to hear your side.

8
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:32,133
Is there something going on
at home that you think is wrong?

9
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,700
Do you think she'll confess?

10
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,767
Where will you take me, if ever?

11
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:37,800
You'll go with us.

12
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,033
We'll take you away from here.

13
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,467
Do you want to go with us, dear?

14
00:01:21,233 --> 00:01:22,333
No.

15
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,533
Are you sure?

16
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:25,300
If she's hurting you...

17
00:01:25,367 --> 00:01:27,433
She's not hurting me.

18
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:30,600
My mom can't do that.

19
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:31,633
She loves me.

20
00:01:33,133 --> 00:01:35,267
And I feel the same way
about her.

21
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:37,333
I love my mom, too.

22
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,433
Where are you taking my
daughter?

23
00:01:54,267 --> 00:01:54,633
Mookie!

24
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:08,100
I can explain.

25
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:12,000
- Whatever she told you...
- I told them the truth, Mommy.

26
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:13,667
What?

27
00:02:16,467 --> 00:02:18,367
That you're not hurting me.

28
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:23,467
That the person...

29
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:27,733
who reported
you is mistaken.

30
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:34,333
Some people probably
don't understand

31
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,367
the way you take care of her.

32
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:39,300
Thank you so much
for the time, Doctor.

33
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:40,700
Sorry for the bother.

34
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:43,000
Yes.
Yes, of course.

35
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:47,367
I apologize for being
such a rude host.

36
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:49,633
I couldn't even prepare
snacks for you.

37
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,133
Don't worry.

38
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,667
I'll just send it to
the barangay hall?

39
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:54,733
No need, Ma'am.

40
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:57,067
We're just doing our job.

41
00:02:57,133 --> 00:02:57,733
Thank you.

42
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,000
We'll get going.

43
00:02:59,967 --> 00:03:05,367
Mookie, you can ask us
for help if you need it.

44
00:03:06,667 --> 00:03:07,500
Thank you.

45
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,100
Bye.

46
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,367
Thank you.

47
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,433
Thank you, Mookie.

48
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,267
Thank you.

49
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:32,400
Thank you.

50
00:03:46,367 --> 00:03:47,333
Are you sure?

51
00:03:48,133 --> 00:03:52,033
Did Mookie really say her
mother doesn't hurt her?

52
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:56,367
Yes. The councilor who talked
to Mookie told me.

53
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:58,633
I just finished talking
to him over the phone.

54
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:01,333
Dan, sorry.

55
00:04:02,633 --> 00:04:04,200
I don't know.

56
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:05,300
I made a mistake.

57
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:09,400
I didn't consider that Mookie
isn't ready yet to speak up.

58
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,367
It has happened already.

59
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:14,633
There's nothing we
can do about it.

60
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,200
She's probably so scared
of her mother.

61
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:19,500
That's why she couldn't
speak up.

62
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:22,500
Aren't you the one
who reported it?

63
00:04:23,733 --> 00:04:26,333
Are you doubting me, too?

64
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,667
I'm not doing anything.

65
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,167
You're just
being paranoid.

66
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,667
I was just testing you.

67
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:38,267
I know who the culprit is.

68
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,033
Damn that Emma.

69
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:43,600
The nerve of her to report me.

70
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:47,067
How would Emma do that?

71
00:04:47,133 --> 00:04:48,300
She's in prison.

72
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:52,567
I'm sure she found a way.

73
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:56,167
She's the only one I know
who has issues with me.

74
00:04:57,133 --> 00:04:58,600
- Of course.
- Mom.

75
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,167
That's her mother.

76
00:05:04,067 --> 00:05:05,200
She's her family.

77
00:05:05,267 --> 00:05:07,100
She won't betray her mother.

78
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:11,367
Does she think my daughter
will take her side?

79
00:05:12,133 --> 00:05:15,600
Frankly, we don't
know that, Olive.

80
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:18,433
Maybe Emma has already
influenced Mookie.

81
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:19,967
She didn't say
anything earlier.

82
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:23,333
But what if she
speaks up next time?

83
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:26,667
Mom, that's wrong.

84
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:29,100
She shouldn't consider her
mother as family

85
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:30,333
if she's hurting her.

86
00:05:31,067 --> 00:05:37,467
Emma, no matter what you say,
Olive is still Mookie's mother.

87
00:05:37,567 --> 00:05:39,533
Not you.

88
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:43,367
Of course, the daughter
will take her mother's side.

89
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:44,567
Not yours.

90
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:48,000
Look what happened to you.

91
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:52,100
Your fighting for her, but
who did she side with?

92
00:05:52,167 --> 00:05:53,200
Did she side with you?

93
00:05:53,267 --> 00:05:55,367
Mom, this is not a game.

94
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:57,967
We're talking about
the kid's life.

95
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:01,467
Now, I'm scared.

96
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:04,167
I don't know what can
her mother do to her.

97
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:05,100
You know what?

98
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:09,267
Focus on getting out

99
00:06:09,367 --> 00:06:12,267
of here instead of interfering
in someone else's life.

100
00:06:18,067 --> 00:06:19,500
That's not going to happen.

101
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:23,300
Mookie won't betray me.

102
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:29,633
I didn't raise her to do that.

103
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,233
In a perfect world...

104
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:39,033
you'll be right.

105
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,733
But in real life,
you'll never know.

106
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:45,500
There are lots of instances that
you can be reported, Olive.

107
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:48,133
And it doesn't have
to come from Mookie.

108
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,167
Some other people can do it.

109
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:51,267
So be careful.

110
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:53,533
I have to go.

111
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:21,633
Mookie, why aren't you
using your crutches?

112
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:29,300
I can now walk without it.

113
00:07:30,133 --> 00:07:31,733
Only mommy doesn't
want me to walk

114
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,433
because she says it's bad for
me.

115
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:40,333
Maybe it's really
bad for your body.

116
00:07:44,767 --> 00:07:46,000
I don't think so.

117
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,633
How can I be able to walk?

118
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:54,100
How can I exercise my legs
if I don't walk, right?

119
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,400
Yeah, you have a point.

120
00:07:58,633 --> 00:08:01,667
Okay, but don't let
your mom see you.

121
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:05,033
She's not here, Flor.

122
00:08:05,733 --> 00:08:11,133
Mookie, it's not that
I want to betray your mom.

123
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:15,333
But you had your chance
to report her.

124
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,000
Why didn't you do that?

125
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:24,400
Actually, I almost did it.

126
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:28,367
I can't blame you if you did.

127
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:31,433
But I thought...

128
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:36,533
it would make me a bad daughter
if I would report her.

129
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:42,033
I realized I couldn't
do that to her.

130
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:46,100
My mom is the...

131
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,433
only person
who cared for me my whole life.

132
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:53,000
She's my only family.

133
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:57,367
Who will take care
of me if I lose her?

134
00:08:58,767 --> 00:09:00,433
I understand you.

135
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:07,200
I will also lose my job
if that happens.

136
00:09:07,267 --> 00:09:08,233
Right?

137
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:12,067
But...

138
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:19,700
I know that my mom loves me.

139
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:20,967
And I love her, too.

140
00:09:21,867 --> 00:09:29,167
But if sometimes I see her
as my caretaker...

141
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:32,367
what does that mean?

142
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:35,000
Is that love?

143
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,233
Or does it mean
I only need her?

144
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,600
That's deep.

145
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:44,300
Do you like some smoothie?

146
00:09:44,367 --> 00:09:47,467
I know you like it.

147
00:09:47,533 --> 00:09:48,133
I can have some.

148
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,367
Okay. I'll make one for you.

149
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:51,300
Smile, okay?

150
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:53,433
You're so pretty.

151
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,467
Don't go anywhere.

152
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:02,600
Mookie!

153
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:06,400
I have a surprise for you.

154
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:13,367
I know you've long been
wanting to have pets.

155
00:10:13,433 --> 00:10:16,733
But you're allergic
to dog and cat fur.

156
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,500
So...

157
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:20,433
I get this for you. Birds.

158
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:22,233
Because I know you like birds.

159
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,200
And here.

160
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:25,767
Not one, but two!

161
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:27,333
I will have them here
in the porch.

162
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:28,133
Come, come!

163
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,233
Come here.

164
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:30,467
I will find a...

165
00:10:31,267 --> 00:10:32,333
Right here.

166
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:34,667
This is a perfect spot.

167
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:37,533
There.

168
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,767
So that you can look at
them anytime you want.

169
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,000
Mookie?

170
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:54,600
Don't I deserve a thank you?

171
00:10:54,667 --> 00:10:56,100
Thank you, Mommy.

172
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:05,000
But to be honest, I don't
want to see birds in cages.

173
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:10,100
They're just birds.

174
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:16,067
How do we get to keep them
if we don't put them in a cage?

175
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,533
That's the point, Mommy.

176
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:20,167
We don't.

177
00:11:20,233 --> 00:11:24,167
So I hope they can be freed.

178
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:26,433
Well...

179
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:31,100
I don't think the pet store

180
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:33,400
where I got them
accepts a refund.

181
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,533
I'll just release
them later.

182
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,633
Mommy...

183
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:43,800
can I have another request?

184
00:11:43,867 --> 00:11:45,267
What is it?

185
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:48,100
Please don't get mad.

186
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:49,433
Just get to the point.

187
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,767
What do you need, Mookie?

188
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:58,500
When the barangay
officials talked to me,

189
00:11:58,567 --> 00:12:04,100
they asked me if I wanted
to go with them.

190
00:12:05,233 --> 00:12:07,567
And I told them no.

191
00:12:07,633 --> 00:12:09,433
Before they left,

192
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:15,733
they told me they were always
there for me

193
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,633
if I needed anything.

194
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:23,433
And, Mommy, I did
what you told me.

195
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:27,267
I thanked them.

196
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:27,967
Good.

197
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:32,167
I'm so proud of you for doing
the right thing, Mookie.

198
00:12:33,067 --> 00:12:39,333
And because of that,
I am going to you give a reward.

199
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:41,733
What do you like?

200
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:42,333
Just tell me.

201
00:12:45,167 --> 00:12:52,333
It's more of a gift
than a reward, Mommy.

202
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:55,300
Can you...

203
00:12:57,233 --> 00:13:04,000
Can you drop the case
against Emma?

204
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:07,233
Please, Mommy?

205
00:13:22,133 --> 00:13:25,567
Of all the things you
can ask me, why is that?

206
00:13:27,733 --> 00:13:30,633
Why do you want me to drop
the case against Emma?

207
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,633
Mommy...

208
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:39,267
I respect you.

209
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:41,500
I really do.

210
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:45,400
And I don't want
to lie to you.

211
00:13:47,767 --> 00:13:50,733
But I feel like this is
the right thing to do, Mommy.

212
00:13:52,267 --> 00:13:55,600
It'll be unfair for Emma
if she'll get blamed.

213
00:13:56,767 --> 00:14:02,167
And maybe it's my fault.

214
00:14:03,667 --> 00:14:04,533
What do you mean?

215
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,500
Maybe it was me who
misplaced my necklace.

216
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:13,200
Maybe I left or lost
it in the dark room.

217
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:18,667
It'll be unfair for Emma
if she'll get blamed for it.

218
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,267
Just like the birds, Mommy.

219
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:34,033
I think if they can talk,
they will ask us to free them.

220
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:43,433
So, Mommy, can we
release the birds now?

221
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,067
Fine.

222
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,533
I already gave
you my word.

223
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,333
Of course, I will keep it.

224
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:55,033
Thank you, Mommy.

225
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:07,000
Mommy...

226
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:10,133
can you help me?

227
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:32,033
Bye, birds.

228
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:34,700
Fly free.

229
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:45,567
Mommy, I hope you do
the same thing to Emma.

230
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:10,067
You've been quiet.

231
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:13,633
Aren't you happy we're home?

232
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,033
I am.

233
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:23,133
But I'm worried.

234
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,400
I wonder why Ma'am Olive
withdrew the case.

235
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:34,067
Maybe she ate
a banana plant.

236
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:36,967
And she's grown a heart.

237
00:16:40,133 --> 00:16:41,233
I'm just joking.

238
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:50,033
I have a feeling that Mookie has
something to do with it.

239
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,067
I've been feeling restless.

240
00:16:51,133 --> 00:16:53,033
I'm worried that her
mother is doing something

241
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,133
to her again.

242
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,067
You did your best, didn't you?

243
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,333
So, please!

244
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,200
Leave them alone.

245
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:10,167
You'll only make
things worse!

246
00:17:10,233 --> 00:17:12,533
I'm worried for Mookie!

247
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,600
This is unbelievable.

248
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:21,000
You're thinking about
nothing but Mookie again!

249
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:26,033
I thought we'd be okay
when we moved to this house.

250
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:28,467
I was convinced that
we would be okay.

251
00:17:28,533 --> 00:17:29,700
And then this.

252
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:33,067
You think about nothing
but Mookie.

253
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,167
Dan, wait.

254
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:36,567
What are you talking about?

255
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:37,200
Aren't we okay?

256
00:17:37,267 --> 00:17:39,533
We don't have any problem.

257
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:44,433
I let you grieve for Baby Kayla
for how many years, right?

258
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:49,533
I understand that you can't just
overcome the sadness overnight.

259
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:56,200
But, Emma...

260
00:17:56,267 --> 00:17:57,733
I'm still here.

261
00:18:00,033 --> 00:18:03,033
I want to fix our life...

262
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,100
our life together.

263
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,433
What do you mean?

264
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:11,133
I want us to have
a better life.

265
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:15,167
I want us to put up a business.

266
00:18:17,233 --> 00:18:21,433
I want us to have a little
house we can call our own.

267
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,400
And we don't have to rent.

268
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:28,000
Sometimes, I want us to go out.

269
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:33,167
I want us to go to the
beach or to Baguio.

270
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:34,700
That's what we're
supposed to be doing.

271
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:39,467
That's what I want to do.

272
00:18:39,533 --> 00:18:41,733
We should enjoy life.

273
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,633
That's what a normal
married life is.

274
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:45,967
Dan...

275
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:49,067
Dan, you know me.

276
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:51,567
Material things
don't matter to me.

277
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:54,267
I'm happy that we're together.

278
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,667
I'm happy with what we have.

279
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,600
Emma, I'm not.

280
00:19:06,167 --> 00:19:08,433
I want you to be with me.

281
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,967
I want you to be on
board with my plans.

282
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:16,433
Emma, please help me.

283
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:20,500
Please put us first.

284
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:27,300
You and me, our life together.

285
00:19:43,633 --> 00:19:45,700
I know I fell
short as a wife.

286
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:50,967
And forgive me if
you feel alone.

287
00:19:51,667 --> 00:19:55,400
I want you to be happy.

288
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:57,667
I want you to
fulfill your dreams.

289
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:00,567
Don't worry.

290
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:03,467
I'll be with you.

291
00:20:03,533 --> 00:20:05,633
I'll be with you
until the end.

292
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:07,667
But...

293
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:13,100
I hope you won't take my concern
for Mookie the wrong way.

294
00:20:14,433 --> 00:20:16,433
Because that will never go away.

295
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:33,600
Imagine?

296
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:36,733
My daughter is blackmailing me.

297
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:38,400
That's expected.
She takes after you.

298
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:42,567
Can I give you some
unsolicited advice?

299
00:20:44,533 --> 00:20:46,333
Go ahead. I'm listening.

300
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:50,400
It'll be a lose-lose situation

301
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:53,167
for you if you pursue
your case against Emma.

302
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:56,633
Bad publicity for you
and Artemis Pharmacy.

303
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:58,667
Do you want the media
to pick on you?

304
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,067
Of course not.

305
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:05,300
Then, drop the
charges against Emma.

306
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:08,000
That's also what Mookie
requests from you.

307
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,433
Request?

308
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,367
More of like a demand.

309
00:21:11,433 --> 00:21:13,200
She just said it nicely.

310
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:16,500
Mookie knows she
has the advantage.

311
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:20,100
You wouldn't want her to carry
out her threat against you.

312
00:21:20,167 --> 00:21:22,600
What if she reports
you to the authorities?

313
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:27,067
I have to make sure that
she doesn't squeal.

314
00:21:28,267 --> 00:21:31,733
I'll make sure that
she can't report me.

315
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:35,400
Mommy Emma, I miss you so much.

316
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:39,133
I want to see you
and be with you.

317
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:44,100
You know, when mommy asked me
what gift I wanted,

318
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,133
I asked her to let you go home.

319
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,733
Promise, Mommy Emma.

320
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:52,367
I will get better.

321
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:55,467
I will make it my life goal.

322
00:22:56,433 --> 00:22:58,567
So that when I turn 18,

323
00:22:58,633 --> 00:23:03,100
when I become an adult,
I can be with you anytime.

324
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:06,000
We'll always be together.

325
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:19,533
I will miss you...

326
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:21,633
so much.

327
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:26,233
Why does she remind
me of my child?

328
00:23:28,133 --> 00:23:34,233
If only my daughter was alive,
you two would be friends.

329
00:23:35,133 --> 00:23:42,067
Whenever I imagine
my grown-up daughter,

330
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:47,367
I see you, Mookie.

331
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,000
Emma.

332
00:24:01,467 --> 00:24:02,333
That's enough.

333
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:04,167
Please stop.

334
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:46,733
Why are you still awake?

335
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:50,000
Didn't I tell you that
you can't stay up late?

336
00:24:52,567 --> 00:24:54,300
I'm waiting for you, Mommy.

337
00:24:57,400 --> 00:25:01,500
Do you want to know if
I did what you wanted?

338
00:25:03,633 --> 00:25:04,633
Well...

339
00:25:07,233 --> 00:25:10,433
as much as I'm right
most of the time,

340
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:15,567
I have to admit that
I also make mistakes.

341
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:18,300
So maybe you're right.

342
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,667
Maybe it wasn't Emma
who took your necklace.

343
00:25:22,533 --> 00:25:24,700
So, there.

344
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:29,100
I dropped the charges
against her.

345
00:25:31,133 --> 00:25:32,300
Really, Mommy?

346
00:25:34,433 --> 00:25:37,067
Will Emma be free?

347
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,267
Isn't that what
you asked me for?

348
00:25:41,767 --> 00:25:43,267
So that's what I did.

349
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:50,733
I want you to be
happy, Mookie.

350
00:25:52,667 --> 00:25:54,500
That's all I want for you.

351
00:25:56,067 --> 00:25:57,300
Thank you, Mommy.

352
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:10,100
And I hope, Mookie,
that you'll always remember...

353
00:26:12,433 --> 00:26:19,467
that I will do anything
and everything for you.

354
00:26:43,167 --> 00:26:45,233
Don't you love me anymore, Mom?

355
00:26:45,300 --> 00:26:47,400
You told me you love me.

356
00:26:47,467 --> 00:26:49,200
Why are you going
to leave me?

357
00:26:49,267 --> 00:26:51,200
Why are you going away?

358
00:26:51,267 --> 00:26:52,500
What's going on with Mookie?

359
00:26:52,567 --> 00:26:53,533
Why, Ma'am?

360
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:56,067
She was down when I saw her.

361
00:26:56,133 --> 00:26:57,633
She also doesn't want to eat.

362
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:00,367
I also saw her crying earlier.

363
00:27:00,433 --> 00:27:02,100
Did something happen
when I was away?

364
00:27:02,167 --> 00:27:03,200
That's what I'm telling you.

365
00:27:03,267 --> 00:27:05,233
You wouldn't be like that

366
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:08,033
if you stayed out of that
child's life.

367
00:27:08,100 --> 00:27:10,133
She cries as if she's lost
a child.

368
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:15,033
Mommy Emma, why did you come
back just to leave me again?

369
00:27:16,267 --> 00:27:18,300
Why do you have to say goodbye?

370
00:27:18,367 --> 00:27:20,067
I now agree with what you want.

371
00:27:20,133 --> 00:27:22,400
We can now move out.

372
00:27:22,467 --> 00:27:23,367
Mookie?

373
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:26,233
You can get up now?

374
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:29,333
Since when?
